<h1><span id="Sicilian_Defence.2C_Najdorf.2C_Opocensky_Variation"></span><span id="Sicilian_Defence,_Najdorf,_Opocensky_Variation">Sicilian Defence, Najdorf, Opocensky Variation</span></h1>
<p>Moves: 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be2
</p><p>6. Be2 is not played as often in response to black pushing 5. ...a6 as is 6. Bg5 or 6. Be3, but it is a solid move. White's bishop at e2 can keep an eye on g4 while allowing for a king side castle.
</p>
<p><b>1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6. Be2</b>
</p>
